---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<DocsLayout title="API Key Management" activeNav="api-keys" description="Scoped API keys with SHA-256 hashing, expiration support, and pluggable storage.">

  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Araxys provides a complete API key management system with <strong>256-bit entropy</strong> keys, <strong>SHA-256 hashing</strong> (raw keys are never persisted), <strong>scope-based authorization</strong>, and configurable expiration.
  </p>

  <h2 id="creating-keys">Creating API Keys</h2>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code set:html={`<span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys <span class="token-keyword">import</span> Scope

<span class="token-comment"># Create a key with specific scopes</span>
key = <span class="token-keyword">await</span> shield.api_key_manager.<span class="token-function">create_key</span>(
    <span class="token-param">owner</span>=<span class="token-string">"service-a"</span>,
    <span class="token-param">scopes</span>=[Scope.READ, Scope.WRITE],
    <span class="token-param">ttl_days</span>=<span class="token-number">90</span>,
    <span class="token-param">label</span>=<span class="token-string">"Production key for Service A"</span>,
)
<span class="token-builtin">print</span>(<span class="token-string">f"Save this key: {key.raw_key}"</span>)  <span class="token-comment"># Shown only once!</span>`} /></pre>
  </div>

  <div class="alert">
    <div class="alert-title">
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size: 16px;">warning</span>
      Critical
    </div>
    <div class="alert-content">
      The raw API key is only available in the creation response. Araxys stores a <strong>SHA-256 hash</strong> — the original key cannot be recovered. Make sure to save it securely.
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="protecting-endpoints">Protecting Endpoints</h2>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code set:html={`<span class="token-keyword">from</span> fastapi <span class="token-keyword">import</span> Depends
<span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys <span class="token-keyword">import</span> Scope
<span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys.api_keys.dependencies <span class="token-keyword">import</span> require_api_key
<span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys.api_keys.models <span class="token-keyword">import</span> APIKeyRecord

<span class="token-decorator">@app.get</span>(<span class="token-string">"/data"</span>)
<span class="token-keyword">async def</span> <span class="token-function">get_data</span>(
    <span class="token-param">key</span>: APIKeyRecord = <span class="token-function">Depends</span>(
        <span class="token-function">require_api_key</span>(Scope.READ, <span class="token-param">manager</span>=shield.api_key_manager)
    ),
):
    <span class="token-keyword">return</span> {"data": "protected", "owner": key.owner}`} /></pre>
  </div>

  <p>The client sends the API key in the <code>X-API-Key</code> header. Araxys hashes the incoming key and looks it up in storage.</p>

  <h2 id="key-security">Security Model</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>256-bit entropy</strong>: Keys are generated with <code>secrets.token_urlsafe</code></li>
    <li><strong>SHA-256 hashing</strong>: Only the hash is stored — raw key is never persisted</li>
    <li><strong>Prefix identification</strong>: Each key has a readable prefix (e.g., <code>arx_a1b2c3</code>) for identification without exposing the full key</li>
    <li><strong>Scope enforcement</strong>: Keys can only access endpoints matching their assigned scopes</li>
    <li><strong>Expiration</strong>: Configurable TTL with automatic rejection of expired keys</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="custom-storage">Custom Storage Backend</h2>
  <p>Implement the <code>APIKeyStorage</code> protocol to persist keys in your database:</p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code><span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys.api_keys.storage <span class="token-keyword">import</span> APIKeyStorage
<span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys.api_keys.models <span class="token-keyword">import</span> APIKeyRecord

<span class="token-keyword">class</span> <span class="token-class">PostgresKeyStorage</span>:
    <span class="token-string">"""Store API keys in PostgreSQL."""</span>

    <span class="token-keyword">async def</span> <span class="token-function">save</span>(<span class="token-param">self</span>, <span class="token-param">record</span>: APIKeyRecord) -> <span class="token-keyword">None</span>:
        ...

    <span class="token-keyword">async def</span> <span class="token-function">get_by_hash</span>(<span class="token-param">self</span>, <span class="token-param">key_hash</span>: <span class="token-builtin">str</span>) -> APIKeyRecord | <span class="token-keyword">None</span>:
        ...

    <span class="token-keyword">async def</span> <span class="token-function">revoke</span>(<span class="token-param">self</span>, <span class="token-param">prefix</span>: <span class="token-builtin">str</span>) -> <span class="token-builtin">bool</span>:
        ...

<span class="token-comment"># Pass to shield</span>
shield = <span class="token-function">AraxysShield</span>(app, config, <span class="token-param">api_key_storage</span>=<span class="token-function">PostgresKeyStorage</span>())</code></pre>
  </div>

  <h2 id="audit-events">Audit Events</h2>
  <p>The API key module generates these audit events:</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Event Type</th>
        <th>When</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>API_KEY_CREATED</code></td><td>A new API key is generated</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>API_KEY_REVOKED</code></td><td>An API key is revoked</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>API_KEY_VERIFIED</code></td><td>A valid API key is used successfully</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>API_KEY_REJECTED</code></td><td>An invalid, expired, or insufficient-scope key is rejected</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

</DocsLayout>
